<subSubSection id="58B9A6E83F071AB93578015BA020FF20" pageId="1" pageNumber="28" type="notes">
<paragraph id="42B78C466723A203352923A0E53AF1F8" pageId="1" pageNumber="28">Notes.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="AD9719CC9835BBB041D9D9CCE2AAFE63" pageId="1" pageNumber="28">
<bibRefCitation id="3B36C0B9B555EEB91DF6B1BF1E3DECD1" DOI="https://doi.org/10.2307/3667210" author="Robyns, A" journalOrPublisher="Bulletin du Jardin Botanique de l'Etat a Bruxelles" pageId="3" pageNumber="30" pagination="1 - 315" refId="B2" refString="Robyns, A, 1963. Essai de Monographie du genre Bombax L. s.l. (Bombacaceae). Bulletin du Jardin Botanique de l'Etat a Bruxelles 33: 1 - 315, DOI: https://doi.org/10.2307/3667210" title="Essai de Monographie du genre Bombax L. s. l. (Bombacaceae)." url="https://doi.org/10.2307/3667210" volume="33" year="1963">Robyns (1963)</bibRefCitation>
proposed 
<taxonomicName id="07D6C561216C308755486A6DB47662C2" authorityName="Carvalho-Sobrinho &amp; Dorr" authorityYear="2017" baseAuthorityName="Carv. - Sobr., comb. &amp;" baseAuthorityYear="2017" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Malvaceae" genus="Pseudobombax" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Pseudobombax grandiflorum subsp. var. var. majus" order="Malvales" pageId="1" pageNumber="28" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="variety" species="grandiflorum" subSpecies="var." variety="majus">Pseudobombax grandiflorum var. majus</taxonomicName>
based on specimens with longer pedicels and staminal tubes as well as wider calyces and petals than are found in the nominate variety. Analysis of the protologue and type material of this variety and the nominate one, along with a comprehensive examination of herbarium specimens, reveals that 
<taxonomicName id="B10E8916B5B00BD295EA2DF5B791EE91" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Malvaceae" genus="P." higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="P. grandiflorum subsp. var. var. majus" order="Malvales" pageId="1" pageNumber="28" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="variety" species="grandiflorum" subSpecies="var." variety="majus">P. grandiflorum var. majus</taxonomicName>
is also morphologically distinct from the nominate variety in having mostly 9-11 (vs. mostly 5) leaflets (7 leaflets rarely occur in both taxa), often 3-7-flowered cymes (vs. flowers solitary, rarely 2-3-flowered cymes), and 5-angulate (vs. 5-costate) fruits in cross-section. Moreover, 
<taxonomicName id="5549E8CA4156FFFAEED268F6FAB0874C" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Malvaceae" genus="P." higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="P. grandiflorum subsp. var. var. majus" order="Malvales" pageId="1" pageNumber="28" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="variety" species="grandiflorum" subSpecies="var." variety="majus">P. grandiflorum var. majus</taxonomicName>
has calyces that are urceolate (vs. cupuliform) and often lobed (vs. truncate).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="63C45978C74E5BAC9B9A8116B7B3DD69" pageId="1" pageNumber="28">
In addition to these morphological differences, the two taxa can be distinguished by their distribution in Eastern Brazil. 
<taxonomicName id="0F3EF1A05149283F8C4F79C3D23AC3F5" authorityName="Carvalho-Sobrinho &amp; Dorr" authorityYear="2017" baseAuthorityName="Carv. - Sobr., comb. &amp;" baseAuthorityYear="2017" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Malvaceae" genus="Pseudobombax" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Pseudobombax grandiflorum subsp. var. var. majus" order="Malvales" pageId="1" pageNumber="28" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="variety" species="grandiflorum" subSpecies="var." variety="majus">Pseudobombax grandiflorum var. majus</taxonomicName>
inhabits semi-deciduous forests and occasionally granitic outcrops in wet forests whereas the nominate variety inhabits mainly coastal restinga vegetation. Thus, morphological evidence along with the parapatric distribution are sufficient to recognize 
<taxonomicName id="F4C6F16DB47A7D15F4C458F8963644D2" authorityName="Carvalho-Sobrinho &amp; Dorr" authorityYear="2017" baseAuthorityName="Carv. - Sobr., comb. &amp;" baseAuthorityYear="2017" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Malvaceae" genus="Pseudobombax" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Pseudobombax grandiflorum subsp. var. var. majus" order="Malvales" pageId="1" pageNumber="28" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="variety" species="grandiflorum" subSpecies="var." variety="majus">Pseudobombax grandiflorum var. majus</taxonomicName>
at species rank.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="F8032F5203DB93F7A08DDB95F64FC16E" pageId="1" pageNumber="28">
<taxonomicName id="71A45D76C14EB857F23D0D122BB5414B" authorityName="Carv. - Sobr., comb. &amp;" authorityYear="2017" baseAuthorityName="Carvalho-Sobrinho &amp; Dorr" baseAuthorityYear="2017" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Malvaceae" genus="Pseudobombax" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Pseudobombax majus" order="Malvales" pageId="1" pageNumber="28" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="majus">
<emphasis id="FF7819B276D600DA1AAA800B6BC2EFC2" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="28">Pseudobombax majus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
can be distinguished from its sister species 
<taxonomicName id="D3BD2EBEEDCDAA908D31F884A0015012" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Malvaceae" genus="P." higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="P. longiflorum" order="Malvales" pageId="1" pageNumber="28" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="longiflorum">
<emphasis id="BADD8B889AC371867E8C9BA6C4DE42AF" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="28">P. longiflorum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Mart.) A. Robyns (
<bibRefCitation id="6D7081F42EC8CA7645E174BFE064FBCE" DOI="https://doi.org/10.1016/j.ympev.2016.05.006" author="Carvalho-Sobrinho, JG" journalOrPublisher="Molecular Phylogenetics and Evolution" pageId="3" pageNumber="30" pagination="56 - 74" refId="B1" refString="Carvalho-Sobrinho, JG, Alverson, WS, Alcantara, S, Queiroz, LP, Mota, AC, Baum, DA, 2016. Revisiting the phylogeny of Bombacoideae (Malvaceae): Novel relationships, morphologically cohesive clades, and a new tribal classification based on multilocus phylogenetic analyses. Molecular Phylogenetics and Evolution 101: 56 - 74, DOI: https://doi.org/10.1016/j.ympev.2016.05.006" title="Revisiting the phylogeny of Bombacoideae (Malvaceae): Novel relationships, morphologically cohesive clades, and a new tribal classification based on multilocus phylogenetic analyses." url="https://doi.org/10.1016/j.ympev.2016.05.006" volume="101" year="2016">Carvalho-Sobrinho et al. 2016</bibRefCitation>
: fig. 2), a widespread species in South American savannas, by its cuneate (vs. truncate) leaflets, shorter (c. 10 vs. 16-50 mm long) petiolules, and its 5-angulate (vs. circular) fruits in cross-section.
</paragraph>
